!! Opening the Backup History Window

Click "Workspace → View Backup History" in the top menu to open the Git history log window.

!! Browsing Commits

* The left panel shows all Git commits in reverse chronological order
* Each entry shows the commit time and message
* If there are uncommitted changes, an "Uncommitted Changes" row appears at the top automatically

!! Viewing Files Changed in a Commit

Click any commit row; the right panel lists the filenames changed in that commit.

!! Committing Current Changes Now

# Click the "Uncommitted Changes" row
# Switch to the "Actions" tab on the right
# Click the "Commit Now" button
# If [[TidGi Feature Handbook/AI Assistant/AI Auto-Generate Backup Title]] is enabled, the commit message is written by the AI automatically

!! Notes

* This window is read-only; it does not support rollback or checking out historical versions (use `git checkout` from the command line for that)
* To push commits to a remote repository, use "Workspace → Sync to Cloud Now"
